Describe the scope of the changes or the problem that these changes wants
to solve.


Changes
=======

Describe how the problem was fixed.

No need to describe the changes in a human readable way.
The changes should be easy to understand just by reading the diff.
If any extra comments are required, add them to the code itself.

List all changes for which an *ideal* solution was not found and compare them
with the current solution.

What was not yet done and link to the ticket for the still to do work.

As a drive-by change add comments about out-of-scope minor drive-by changes.


